g.text: Video Revachol, 24h: "*Something?* Listen, I can't help you." He sounds annoyed now. "If you need further assistance you can visit us on the corner of Voyager and Main. Are we done?"
Empathy: He thinks you're pulling a prank on him.
You: "My name is Raphaël Ambrosius Costeau. Do you have anything on my name?"

Video Revachol, 24h: "Raphaël *what*? Listen, I can't help you over the phone." He sounds annoyed now. "If you need further assistance you can visit us on the corner of Voyager and Main. Are we done?"
You: I might try this again later.
Interfacing: Sure, why not. Muscle memory is a tricky thing.
Physical Instrument: Nothing tricky about that. You just *do*, *fail*, *repeat* until it works. All it takes is motivation and practice.
Punch Clock/Payphone: The machine swallows your coin and seems to be waiting for your next move.
Video Revachol, 24h: "If you can, return it to us on the corner of Voyager and Main."

Shivers: On the corner of Voyager and Main a large neon sign hangs on the side of a building: "Video Revachol, 24h." It's raining and there is almost no traffic on the street. A woman's footprints in the mud lead away from the front door.
Shivers: Tiny heels, tip-toeing down the road. Beautiful steps, light-footed, with a lifetime ahead of them. You look up and the air seems to grow darker.
Video Revachol, 24h: The call is terminated by the other party. You're left with the discomforting sound of the disconnect tone.
Punch Clock/Payphone: An imposing combination of a punch-clock and a payphone is looking down at you from the wall. A note on the side says: "Tokens unavailable due to strike. Use change."
Punch Clock/Payphone: The already familiar cold touch of plastic welcomes you as you pick up the handset.
You: "We're done." Hang up the phone. [Leave.]
You: "Kim, I feel sad about Video Revachol 24h."
Video Revachol, 24h: "Here we are! You haven't rented anything in five years, but you still have a copy of *Blue Ocean Hell* from November '46. Wooh, not a fun film, that one."
You: "What kind of a film is that?"
Punch Clock/Payphone: The payphone hangs mutely on the wall. There isn't much more to do here.
Perception (Hearing): The voice of a youngster on the other end sounds as enthusiastic as that of a man walking towards the gallows.
Kim Kitsuragi: "That's enough for you today," the lieutenant says quietly. "Let's conclude this call."
Inland Empire: Suddenly you feel like you don't want to hear about video rentals anymore. You don't want to hear about *any of it*. It was all shit. It's over.
You: Let your muscle memory dial a random number.
Video Revachol, 24h: "Sir, I don't know. It's a video rental. Maybe you rent videos here?"
You: "Can't we do it without my last name? I can't really remember it."
Video Revachol, 24h: "Listen, man, I can't help you without your surname." He sounds annoyed now. "If you need further assistance you can visit us on the corner of Voyager and Main. Are we done?"
Interfacing: Your fingers run over the dial pad. 005... that's the dialling code for Revachol -- 49-52... and a moment of hesitation before entering the final numbers: 993.
Interfacing: It's unclear whether you actually have muscle memory. Right now your finger is just drawing vaguely occult patterns in the air.
You: Quietly hang up the phone. [Leave.]
Video Revachol, 24h: "Maybe you called to extend your rental period? Do you need to extend your rental period?"
Video Revachol, 24h: "Video Revachol is a 24 hour video rental. We rent eight and ten millimetre film for home use. This is Lemmy."
You: "No, I meant what is this place to *me*?"
You: "My name is Harry Something. Do you have anything on my name?"
Video Revachol, 24h: "What did you say your last name was?"
Video Revachol, 24h: ...a crackle, someone picks up! They say: "Video Revachol, 24 hour video rental. We rent eight- and ten-millimetre film for home use. This is Lemmy, how may I help you?"
You: "My name is Harry Du Bois. Do you have anything on my name?"
Video Revachol, 24h: "Let me fire up the machine..." Keys are being pressed in the background. "Du Bois... Du Bois..."
Video Revachol, 24h: He concludes: "No wonder no one's been missing it. Still, it would be great if you could return it to us. We're on the corner of Voyager and Main."
You: "My name is Harrier Du Bois. Do you have anything on my name?"
You: "Maybe, but I don't even know my *name*."
Video Revachol, 24h: "If you need any further assistance you can visit us on the corner of Voyager and Main." He sounds annoyed now. "I can't help you over the phone -- are we done?"

Video Revachol, 24h: "Uh... it's not an easy watch." He reads: "'After the death of his daughter and subsequent divorce, Zsiemsk immigrant Igidius Wójcik tries to come to terms with the onset of dementia...'"
